posts.com: A mixed bag of a show. The roulette match was an hour long with about 5 minutes worth of highlights. The end result was pleasant but I can't recommend anyone to watch the whole thing because it turned into a slog and had way too many draws. The triangle derby match was fine and standard. The six-woman tag was good and Konami getting cheered so loudly made me very happy. MIRAI/Chihiro was a great and stiff match that may have been too close, but it made for a lot of entertainment. The tag title match was really good and hard-hitting, albeit a bit cliche, but the result and aftermath was unsatisfying. To this point, the show ranged from good to really good aside for the opening match. Sadly, Saya vs. Momo was a letdown for me, as it never hit the next gear, was really cliche and the finish was bad. So much for the prediction of Momo taking Saya to a draw or looking great in defeat. Saya's reign feels lifeless and dragging at this point. Thankfully the main event was everything it was expected to be, full of violent bumps and crazy moments, while also being paced really well for a 25-minute match. The result was inevitable, but the match delivered. So there were three really good/great matches, a vastly underwhelming match that had the potential to be special, a couple of decent/good matches and an opener that went way too long to be recommended. I guess that makes for a 7/10 rating? It had enough good/great matches to warrant an 8, but also enough disappointments to warrant a 6. The crowd being allowed to cheer was nice, but they were too muted a lot of the time. It was better than nothing though. Just skim the opener, keep expectations severely low for Saya/Momo and enjoy the rest to get the best experience from this show.
